WEBVTT

00:04.770 --> 00:16.166
Hey everyone, I'm Chris Crow, campus pastor for Crossway Christian Church's Millford campus here in Southern New Hampshire, where our mission is all about practicing the way of Jesus together as we pursue God, build community, and unleash compassion.

00:16.186 --> 00:21.193
I pray that what you hear today will help you experience God more deeply and live more and more like Jesus.

00:21.233 --> 00:25.579
Good morning.

00:26.901 --> 00:32.248
Let's take our Bibles this morning and turn to Psalm 23 and we'll continue in our series.

00:32.489 --> 00:33.490
Glad to see all of you.

00:34.466 --> 00:36.389
We were at the Deerfield Fair yesterday.

00:36.429 --> 00:40.254
I think all of New Hampshire was there at the same time.

00:40.314 --> 00:42.337
There's a lot of people there.

00:43.419 --> 00:46.163
And so I was thinking, we do what we desire.

00:46.623 --> 00:56.137
And so there's a lot of people that desire to be at the Deerfield Fair and they'll wait in lines for overpriced food and different things like that.

00:56.217 --> 00:59.922
And so it's so good to see you in the house of the Lord because you desire to be here.

01:00.898 --> 01:11.718
And so if more and more Christians would desire the presence of the Lord manifest in the body of Christ or the local church, that would be even more phenomenal.

01:12.960 --> 01:16.667
So thank you for being here to give Jesus the glory that he deserves.

01:17.589 --> 01:19.593
He deserves to be exalted and lifted up.

01:19.673 --> 01:19.953
Amen.

01:20.634 --> 01:21.055
He does.

01:21.095 --> 01:21.837
He does.

01:21.897 --> 01:22.578
He does.

01:23.042 --> 01:24.504
So we're going to continue Psalm 23.

01:24.785 --> 01:27.789
We're titling this series, Experiencing Psalm 23.

01:27.930 --> 01:29.392
We're going to look at verse 2.

01:29.452 --> 01:39.608
If you take your eyes to verse 2 in Psalm 23, David said, He makes me lie down in green pastures and He leads me beside still waters or literally waters of rest.

01:40.569 --> 01:43.674
To understand the Psalm, we've needed to get into the life of David.

01:43.694 --> 01:46.098
Look at his backstory, what he went through.

01:46.466 --> 01:48.608
What he was thinking, tried to get into his head.

01:48.668 --> 01:49.750
David was a fugitive.

01:49.770 --> 01:51.572
You remember the movie, The Fugitive with Harrison Ford?

01:51.672 --> 01:51.992
Anybody?

01:52.333 --> 01:53.234
You'll see an image on here.

01:53.254 --> 01:54.155
You're like, I've never heard of it.

01:54.175 --> 01:55.076
I've never heard of it.

01:55.096 --> 01:55.716
Pull that up there.

01:55.736 --> 01:56.357
It's great.

01:56.537 --> 01:57.398
It's a great movie.

01:58.920 --> 02:02.584
So Harrison Ford is on the run, but he's not on the run for any crime he committed.

02:04.206 --> 02:06.789
People thought that he committed a crime, but he was innocent.

02:06.909 --> 02:07.730
But he's on the run.

02:07.830 --> 02:08.791
David is on the run.

02:09.271 --> 02:10.313
Who's he on the run from?

02:10.353 --> 02:10.993
Does anybody know?

02:12.195 --> 02:12.996
Yeah, King Saul.

02:13.096 --> 02:13.816
For how many years?

02:13.957 --> 02:14.357
Do you remember?

02:14.597 --> 02:15.218
I mentioned that.

02:15.778 --> 02:18.741
20 years, 20 years, having somebody stalk you.

02:19.602 --> 02:20.484
And so he was on a run.

02:20.524 --> 02:26.791
He was a fugitive not for crime, but for jealousy and envy in the heart of King Saul toward David.

02:27.752 --> 02:29.054
And so that must have been a tough road.

02:29.074 --> 02:35.181
So when you get into the life of David trying to understand Psalm 23, it's important to look at where David was in his life.

02:35.381 --> 02:36.182
What was going on?

02:36.242 --> 02:37.203
What was he thinking?

02:37.243 --> 02:38.545
What was he experiencing?

02:39.225 --> 02:43.090
That is all very helpful to understand what we just read in Psalm 23.2.

02:44.418 --> 02:48.202
I've titled the third message in this series, the skill of the shepherd.

02:49.203 --> 02:50.625
The skill of the shepherd.

02:50.645 --> 02:55.230
Now, we're all skilled in various ways, right?

02:55.250 --> 02:57.132
And we value the skills of others.

02:57.453 --> 03:01.697
It matters if your surgeon is skilled, correct?

03:01.717 --> 03:06.162
Now, if your surgeon only had experience maybe playing the game of operation, remember that?

03:06.203 --> 03:12.850
You'd be like, I think I want another surgeon to operate on my brain or my heart or my whatever.

03:13.794 --> 03:15.576
So it's important to have skills.

03:15.656 --> 03:18.059
The pilot flying your plane, skilled or unskilled.

03:20.102 --> 03:21.103
Very skilled, hopefully.

03:21.984 --> 03:37.003
How about the chef preparing your meal or the politician that is leading us or the police force need to be skilled, the military that we have need to be skilled, pastors need to be skilled at what they do as they shepherd the flock.

03:37.063 --> 03:41.048
Parents, you need to be skilled at parenting, your sons and daughters.

03:41.288 --> 03:42.770
We are valuing

03:43.330 --> 03:46.273
the skills of the shepherd today.

03:46.313 --> 03:51.639
How skillful is God in shepherding our souls?

03:51.899 --> 03:52.780
This is important.

03:53.441 --> 03:56.264
You're going to see it in the text as we expound it a little bit.

03:56.284 --> 04:03.352
I'm going to bring two principles, two truths, and then we'll look at two application truths at the very end of this message.

04:03.392 --> 04:03.852
Are you ready?

04:04.953 --> 04:09.138
The Apostle Paul referred to himself as a skilled master builder.

04:09.698 --> 04:11.059
a skilled master builder.

04:11.460 --> 04:14.563
Psalm 78 verse 72, you'll see this up on the screen.

04:14.603 --> 04:15.784
It says this about David.

04:16.204 --> 04:20.849
With upright heart, he shepherded them and guided them with his what?

04:21.549 --> 04:22.650
Skillful hand.

04:23.211 --> 04:24.292
His skillful hand.

04:25.053 --> 04:26.254
So let's look at these principles.

04:26.274 --> 04:26.874
Here's number one.

04:26.894 --> 04:30.217
If you want to write it down, we're going to make available too because we know that there's notetakers.

04:30.818 --> 04:31.719
Is there any notetakers here?

04:31.759 --> 04:32.680
You got to write everything down?

04:33.460 --> 04:33.721
Wow.

04:33.941 --> 04:34.261
Okay.

04:34.301 --> 04:34.642
Over here.

04:34.702 --> 04:36.303
They all kind of gather together.

04:36.323 --> 04:36.884
Is that what you do?

04:37.464 --> 04:39.346
Get community over there.

04:39.522 --> 04:42.926
You're going to find these as you walk in, hopefully in their future.

04:42.966 --> 04:49.554
Back at York Bible Church where I was, people would ask, can you give an outline with blanks and people like to note take?

04:49.574 --> 04:53.418
So you'll see those as you come in, probably beginning next Lord's day.

04:53.919 --> 04:56.742
So for those who are note takers, we'll do that.

04:57.443 --> 04:59.285
So I'm going to give you point number one.

04:59.325 --> 05:00.827
You might want to try to write this down.

05:00.887 --> 05:04.291
God provides for us just enough faith to move forward.

05:05.412 --> 05:06.273
I'm going to repeat that.

05:06.313 --> 05:07.154
That's important.

05:07.522 --> 05:10.485
And this is in verse two, he makes me lie down in green pastor.

05:10.505 --> 05:12.246
So I'm going to show you what I'm talking about there.

05:12.647 --> 05:17.111
Number one, God provides for us just enough faith to move forward.

05:17.131 --> 05:19.573
You're going to need to know that where you're at in your journey.

05:19.593 --> 05:21.055
Now remember, we're understanding David.

05:21.095 --> 05:21.836
David's on the run.

05:21.876 --> 05:24.258
He's going in the caves of a dulum over and over again.

05:24.318 --> 05:25.559
He's a fugitive.

05:26.220 --> 05:29.042
And so he's going into a cave for refuge and protection.

05:29.102 --> 05:29.923
Saul's after him.

05:29.943 --> 05:31.425
He gets word, Saul's getting close.

05:31.485 --> 05:33.487
He leaves the cave of comfort.

05:33.987 --> 05:37.170
And God's going to call you to leave a cave of comfort once in a while.

05:37.506 --> 05:41.850
And to be able to do that, you're going to have to know that God is skilled at shepherding your life.

05:42.691 --> 05:48.758
And when he shows or reveals his skillfulness in your life, then you're going to gain more faith.

05:48.798 --> 05:53.062
You're going to grow not so much from glory to glory, although that's part of the journey.

05:53.382 --> 05:54.824
But you're going to go from faith to faith.

05:54.884 --> 05:57.426
Your faith now, you think, is, well, it's not super strong.

05:58.227 --> 06:04.754
Well, when you see the skillful shepherd's hand, when you need to leave that cave of comfort, and you're going to have to leave it.

06:06.306 --> 06:07.488
This is what David had to do.

06:07.628 --> 06:09.170
He would be king 20 years later.

06:09.631 --> 06:11.433
But he has the anointing, by the way.

06:11.453 --> 06:12.475
He doesn't have the position.

06:13.055 --> 06:13.997
Who has the position?

06:14.678 --> 06:15.779
Saul had the position.

06:15.799 --> 06:16.621
Did he have the anointing?

06:16.641 --> 06:17.101
Yes or no?

06:17.562 --> 06:17.782
No.

06:17.822 --> 06:21.948
And so what you want is you want the anointing more than a position.

06:22.309 --> 06:23.650
Don't be position hungry.

06:24.131 --> 06:25.974
Don't try to jockey for position.

06:26.595 --> 06:28.057
Humble yourselves before the Lord.

06:28.437 --> 06:30.400
And then ask for the anointing on your life.

06:30.941 --> 06:31.922
That's more important.

06:32.770 --> 06:35.894
And so David is understanding the skills of his shepherd.

06:36.214 --> 06:39.138
Now this phrase, he makes me lie down in green pastures.

06:39.198 --> 06:40.740
I look at it and I'm going, interesting.

06:41.341 --> 06:44.966
He makes me lie down in green.

06:46.368 --> 06:48.711
Ask questions with every word of the Bible.

06:49.812 --> 06:52.516
And so when I looked at the text, I'm thinking, okay, why green, Lord?

06:53.357 --> 06:53.978
Is that important?

06:54.018 --> 06:55.179
Does that mean anything?

06:55.199 --> 07:00.466
So you ask yourself questions when you're trying to interpret scripture by the power of the Holy Spirit.

07:00.674 --> 07:02.878
David is being stalked by King Saul.

07:02.898 --> 07:03.379
We know that.

07:03.560 --> 07:04.762
He needs to keep moving.

07:04.822 --> 07:05.944
We see that in his life.

07:06.485 --> 07:09.290
I want to come back to the fact that he has to keep moving.

07:09.331 --> 07:10.353
So hold on to that thought.

07:10.773 --> 07:15.082
But it's important to see that David is saying something here about being calm and content.

07:16.645 --> 07:21.774
Now, when I've looked at this verse through the years, I have an image I want to bring up on the screen if you could bring that.

07:22.095 --> 07:23.698
This is what I would think of.

07:23.842 --> 07:25.444
in terms of this verse.

07:25.484 --> 07:27.587
And I'd be like, oh God, I'm under some serious stress.

07:27.627 --> 07:28.228
Life is hard.

07:28.688 --> 07:30.611
You know, things are going really bad.

07:31.832 --> 07:33.555
You make me lie down in green pastures.

07:33.935 --> 07:40.864
And I would get this vision in my mind of a pastor or a prairie or something beautiful like we're seeing here.

07:41.885 --> 07:43.247
And there is a place for that.

07:44.188 --> 07:48.774
But I don't know if that's the most accurate interpretation of what David is trying to say in Psalm 23.2.

07:49.295 --> 07:51.698
Nothing wrong with it.

07:52.130 --> 07:59.181
Nothing wrong with believing that God's going to lead you to a place like that so that you'll lay down and you'll find calm and you'll find comfort and all those things.

07:59.621 --> 08:01.264
Those are very important things.

08:01.624 --> 08:02.446
Let me give you another image.

08:02.486 --> 08:05.210
I'm going to do a little test with you, a little interactive here.

08:05.590 --> 08:06.852
I want you to bring that up here.

08:06.872 --> 08:10.318
Where would you rather be on the left in that image or would you rather be on the right?

08:10.338 --> 08:11.700
How many people are, yes, I want left.

08:11.740 --> 08:14.043
I want traffic jam, road rage.

08:14.083 --> 08:14.924
I just thrive on that.

08:16.026 --> 08:17.268
No way.

08:17.288 --> 08:19.932
Most of us who want solitude, they want to be calm.

08:19.972 --> 08:21.234
They want to be comforted.

08:21.474 --> 08:24.197
They need primarily the one on the right.

08:24.217 --> 08:27.079
The one on the left is very strenuous and stressful.

08:27.880 --> 08:33.305
And so what we want to try to do is understand that it's right and good to want to be in a prairie or meadow.

08:34.446 --> 08:42.073
You want to be in that place where God brings calm and comfort and contentment that is part of the interpretation.

08:42.894 --> 08:47.058
But that is not the totality of what David is trying to say.

08:47.438 --> 08:51.282
And the reason why I say that is because, again, we have to understand that David is in deserts.

08:51.490 --> 08:52.692
He's in the wilderness.

08:53.292 --> 08:55.355
He's in crags and crevices.

08:55.796 --> 08:57.017
He's hiding in caves.

08:57.718 --> 08:59.260
He's stressed.

08:59.361 --> 09:00.101
He's upset.

09:00.522 --> 09:02.344
He's thinking his life is going to come to an end.

09:02.385 --> 09:03.566
He's thinking about his family.

09:03.887 --> 09:09.053
I mean, he's a man, and he's battling with real, real hard things.

09:11.256 --> 09:15.162
So in that context, I want to give you another angle to look at this.

09:15.342 --> 09:16.163
So hang with me.

09:17.184 --> 09:19.007
You'll notice that these are sheep trails.

09:19.728 --> 09:20.389
That's what they are.

09:20.429 --> 09:21.490
They're sheep trails.

09:22.082 --> 09:27.167
And what a shepherd would do is they'd lead their sheep to these green pastures.

09:27.788 --> 09:31.651
And technically, there wasn't a whole lot of grass in a lot of these places.

09:32.432 --> 09:43.803
But there was enough grass that the shepherd would bring that sheep to, that that sheep would then eat and feel the full of that experience.

09:44.684 --> 09:46.126
And then they would feel that comfort.

09:46.206 --> 09:47.607
But what are they learning?

09:47.647 --> 09:50.450
They're learning the skill of their shepherd.

09:50.786 --> 09:55.513
because what the shepherd will do from there is take that sheep and keep moving them forward.

09:56.435 --> 09:57.677
Some of you don't want to move forward.

09:59.039 --> 10:00.401
Some of you want to stay where you are.

10:01.502 --> 10:04.507
And God's going to say, no, no, I'm calling you out of that cave of comfort.

10:06.490 --> 10:10.556
He's going to lead you to green pastures, but the pastures aren't necessarily what I showed you earlier.

10:10.937 --> 10:12.259
They might look more like this.

10:12.860 --> 10:19.410
And he's going to give you just enough faith for you to move to the next pasture.

10:19.970 --> 10:20.731
Does it make any sense?

10:22.234 --> 10:23.115
And that's how you grow.

10:24.417 --> 10:25.559
That's how you get stronger.

10:27.022 --> 10:31.068
Some of you are not going to grow at all in the coming year.

10:34.093 --> 10:34.334
Why?

10:37.038 --> 10:37.819
Just like a sheep.

10:39.703 --> 10:41.445
Do you know that sheep are mentioned more?

10:41.946 --> 10:44.210
Any animal in all of the Bible, sheep are mentioned the most.

10:45.570 --> 10:46.672
We're prone to wander.

10:46.792 --> 10:47.954
Sheeps are prone to wander.

10:47.974 --> 10:48.895
Anybody prone to wander?

10:49.256 --> 10:50.918
How many people have ever wandered from the Lord?

10:50.938 --> 10:51.379
Raise your hand.

10:51.399 --> 10:52.040
Don't leave me alone.

10:53.221 --> 10:54.223
Because you would be lying.

10:54.263 --> 10:57.087
Everybody has prone to wander.

10:57.127 --> 10:58.750
We're known as sheep in Scripture.

10:59.331 --> 11:00.472
Jesus is our shepherd.

11:00.532 --> 11:02.996
I'm telling you, Jesus is skilled at shepherding our lives.

11:03.917 --> 11:05.380
He is skilled at shepherding your life.

11:06.702 --> 11:07.703
You're going to need to know that.

11:07.883 --> 11:09.746
You're going to need to grow in that.

11:09.806 --> 11:14.994
And that's where David is at in his life and as he's writing these verses.

11:15.458 --> 11:16.919
Let me show you a wonderful picture.

11:16.979 --> 11:18.000
It's a picture of a parent.

11:18.461 --> 11:23.626
A very skilled provider is this young mom with this beautiful little baby.

11:23.686 --> 11:29.111
Now, what can we learn from that in regards to what I'm trying to say here in this first point?

11:29.712 --> 11:31.854
You'll notice that the baby is holding onto a spoon.

11:32.835 --> 11:33.596
Did you pick up on that?

11:34.937 --> 11:44.466
Now, if that baby is skilled or unskilled in feeding itself, unskilled, we'll rely on the parent who is skilled to take care of.

11:45.314 --> 11:45.534
them.

11:47.036 --> 11:50.681
I'm sure if that baby tried to feed themselves, it would be like in the forehead.

11:52.363 --> 11:54.685
Or be in the ear, you know, that kind of thing.

11:55.366 --> 12:01.794
So the baby has to rely on the skill of the parent to feed them.

12:02.375 --> 12:04.017
What's going to happen in the baby's mind?

12:04.277 --> 12:07.441
Can't really talk, I would imagine, at that age, Google and Gaga.

12:07.721 --> 12:09.484
But what's happening inside of their soul?

12:11.466 --> 12:14.770
But they're realizing more that mom is a skilled feeder

12:14.882 --> 12:18.247
of my life, a protector of my life, a provider of my life.

12:18.547 --> 12:20.570
That's the same thing David's talking about.

12:21.972 --> 12:22.793
He leads me.

12:22.833 --> 12:25.637
He makes me lie down in green pastures.

12:25.937 --> 12:29.782
He's going to give me enough faith to go from here to there.

12:30.103 --> 12:33.588
And then when I get there, he's going to give me enough faith to go from there to over there.

12:33.948 --> 12:37.173
And then I'm going to be growing in grace and the knowledge of Jesus Christ.

12:37.693 --> 12:44.082
Not just the knowledge of who He is, doctrinally, but who He is experientially.

12:44.450 --> 12:46.052
that he is a skilled shepherd.

12:46.312 --> 12:48.656
And I'm going to say to you, Jesus, this is what you'll be saying.

12:48.856 --> 12:49.917
You probably already do.

12:50.238 --> 12:51.459
Jesus, you are so skilled.

12:51.479 --> 12:52.461
You know how to lead my life.

12:52.881 --> 12:54.083
You know exactly what you're doing.

12:55.104 --> 12:55.945
I don't have to doubt you.

12:57.727 --> 12:58.248
But you know what?

12:58.268 --> 12:59.810
I've doubted the Lord's skill before.

12:59.850 --> 13:01.412
I have.

13:01.472 --> 13:03.615
I've panicked.

13:03.635 --> 13:04.576
I've gotten nervous.

13:07.120 --> 13:08.101
Anybody else, right?

13:09.443 --> 13:10.244
But then what happens?

13:10.284 --> 13:11.826
He then leads me.

13:12.066 --> 13:13.267
He feeds me.

13:13.307 --> 13:17.011
He brings me to a pastor that I can just take and enjoy.

13:17.031 --> 13:18.672
And I'm like, oh God, you are good.

13:19.253 --> 13:21.395
You know what to give me exactly when I need it.

13:22.736 --> 13:24.298
And then I get stronger in my faith.

13:24.658 --> 13:26.500
And then I leave my cave of comfort.

13:26.520 --> 13:27.361
And I move on.

13:27.961 --> 13:29.022
And then I move on again.

13:29.042 --> 13:32.706
And as I keep moving with the Lord, I keep getting stronger in faith.

13:33.507 --> 13:34.308
This is how he does it.

13:34.328 --> 13:34.888
It's wonderful.

13:36.229 --> 13:39.132
The skill of the shepherd, it's critical to survival.

13:39.152 --> 13:40.914
It's critical to that baby's life.

13:41.378 --> 13:49.226
that they trust their mom and their dads skills in providing for them and feeding them.

13:49.607 --> 13:50.948
God is a provider.

13:50.988 --> 13:52.309
Does anybody know the word for provider?

13:52.950 --> 13:56.814
He is Jehovah Jaira, our provider.

13:57.074 --> 13:58.456
This is the way that God is with us.

13:58.496 --> 13:59.297
He's wonderful.

13:59.637 --> 14:02.640
Now he makes us, you'll notice the text, take your eyes there.

14:02.660 --> 14:05.123
He makes me, boy, that sounds harsh.

14:06.464 --> 14:08.466
I'm telling you it's okay if God makes me do it.

14:09.538 --> 14:10.179
It really is.

14:10.279 --> 14:14.664
Now, if you chafe against that, then you might want to look at your own heart and go, what is it?

14:14.684 --> 14:15.866
Maybe I have a stubborn spirit.

14:17.288 --> 14:19.931
Some people have stubborn spirit, overwhelms them a strong old.

14:20.752 --> 14:22.674
Nobody's going to tell me what to do, even God.

14:23.916 --> 14:26.940
And if God said, I'm going to make you do something, how many people would be like bringing on?

14:27.080 --> 14:27.700
I'm OK with that.

14:28.842 --> 14:29.443
We have to be.

14:30.624 --> 14:31.125
We have to be.

14:31.145 --> 14:33.187
But that's not really what it's talking about there.

14:33.588 --> 14:35.350
It's a wonderful wonder.

14:35.370 --> 14:36.571
He's not forcing us.

14:37.232 --> 14:38.674
This is not who God is.

14:39.266 --> 14:43.934
God lovingly leads us and provides what we need each and every single day.

14:44.315 --> 14:45.417
I don't want you to feel anxious.

14:46.198 --> 14:46.959
I hate anxiety.

14:46.999 --> 14:47.901
Don't you hate anxiety?

14:48.682 --> 14:49.984
Do you need a word from the Lord today?

14:50.044 --> 14:52.789
Three of you need a word from the Lord.

14:52.809 --> 14:53.050
Okay.

14:53.390 --> 14:55.113
I'll talk to just three people in the house.

14:56.095 --> 14:57.617
Do you need a word from the Lord today?

14:57.637 --> 14:59.501
That is good.

14:59.561 --> 15:00.122
That is great.

15:00.142 --> 15:01.384
We're turning a little Pentecostal.

15:01.404 --> 15:01.825
I love it.

15:02.145 --> 15:02.406
Love it.

15:02.886 --> 15:04.449
Little Hooten and Holler and it's not bad.

15:04.509 --> 15:05.010
Let's do it.

15:07.266 --> 15:09.528
Here's what he's talking about here, a green pastor.

15:09.909 --> 15:12.471
This is a place of provision, but watch, watch this.

15:12.531 --> 15:13.092
It's beautiful.

15:13.692 --> 15:14.733
He's talking about the gospel.

15:16.735 --> 15:17.736
This is what he's talking about.

15:20.238 --> 15:22.040
He's going to make you lay down in the gospel.

15:24.502 --> 15:26.124
That's where you're going to find your feeding.

15:26.164 --> 15:29.267
So you weren't just saved by the gospel.

15:29.307 --> 15:31.069
You're sanctified by the gospel.

15:31.309 --> 15:36.754
In other words, you were saved from your sins, from sin, death, hell, and Satan.

15:37.634 --> 15:41.458
That salvation, you were justified by faith alone and Christ alone.

15:42.218 --> 15:43.940
So was I in the gospel.

15:45.221 --> 15:49.425
And that same gospel isn't just to save us, it's to preserve us.

15:50.306 --> 15:51.988
In other words, you feed on the gospel.

15:52.468 --> 15:53.750
This is the beauty of the gospel.

15:54.090 --> 15:55.691
That's why it needs to be preached.

15:57.153 --> 15:59.035
Some of you need to hear the gospel today.

15:59.315 --> 16:01.177
I'm gonna leave you to a green pasture.

16:02.438 --> 16:06.642
You're gonna be able to lay down in the gospel, feed on the gospel,

16:07.266 --> 16:10.591
And you're going to get your faith strengthened as a result of that.

16:10.912 --> 16:11.493
This makes sense?

16:13.336 --> 16:15.119
This is important for us to understand.

16:15.499 --> 16:17.462
I want you to lay down in the gospel.

16:17.502 --> 16:28.179
Now listen, some of you, some of you in the house or maybe watching, don't know Jesus Christ as your shepherd.

16:30.062 --> 16:34.770
It's the gospel that I preach to you that you would repent of your sins.

16:35.586 --> 16:38.209
and put your faith in Him alone because He loves you.

16:38.510 --> 16:39.310
He loves you.

16:39.631 --> 16:43.215
He died on that cross because He loves you.

16:46.259 --> 16:47.440
He's a substitute for you.

16:49.322 --> 16:50.844
You can't get to heaven on your own.

16:51.625 --> 16:53.487
I'm telling you, you're going to fail miserably.

16:57.092 --> 16:58.133
You need Jesus today.

16:59.114 --> 17:00.616
I needed Him at 19 years old.

17:00.676 --> 17:02.258
I need Him every single day since then.

17:05.090 --> 17:05.811
He makes me.

17:06.752 --> 17:07.674
I don't want you to be anxious.

17:07.694 --> 17:10.238
The Bible says be anxious for nothing but in everything by what?

17:10.858 --> 17:12.060
Prayer and supplication.

17:12.100 --> 17:12.942
Here's point number two.

17:13.783 --> 17:16.106
Now this isn't the second phrase that David uses here.

17:16.186 --> 17:17.769
He leads me besides still waters.

17:17.789 --> 17:21.534
Number two, God protects our faith so it won't ultimately fail.

17:22.355 --> 17:22.996
That's number two.

17:25.400 --> 17:28.224
This is gonna bring you some calm and assurance as well, I hope and pray.

17:29.426 --> 17:31.188
What's the key operative word in that phrase?

17:31.269 --> 17:32.791
He leads me besides still waters.

17:32.811 --> 17:34.994
What word stands out to you?

17:35.906 --> 17:37.308
I'm sorry.

17:37.328 --> 17:37.448
Leads.

17:37.468 --> 17:37.789
Leads.

17:37.869 --> 17:38.069
Good.

17:38.269 --> 17:38.670
That's good.

17:39.251 --> 17:39.351
Yeah.

17:39.371 --> 17:39.912
Any other words?

17:41.775 --> 17:42.115
Still.

17:43.217 --> 17:43.517
Still.

17:43.657 --> 17:43.778
Still.

17:43.798 --> 17:45.560
Let me just camp on still for a minute.

17:46.662 --> 17:51.890
He leads me beside still waters, opposite of turbulent, right?

17:52.110 --> 17:53.111
Opposite of rushing waters.

17:53.131 --> 17:55.535
You'll see an image on the screen of a river.

17:55.595 --> 17:59.321
This river would a skilled shepherd lead a sheep to this river.

17:59.381 --> 17:59.861
Yes or no?

18:01.083 --> 18:01.724
Absolutely not.

18:01.804 --> 18:02.405
Why wouldn't they?

18:02.445 --> 18:05.650
Those little legs can't handle that.

18:06.658 --> 18:08.080
they would be swept down river.

18:09.222 --> 18:13.228
There would be fear and terror inside of the sheep's heart and their mind.

18:14.510 --> 18:16.974
David is saying he leads besides still waters.

18:17.014 --> 18:18.156
What is that saying to us?

18:18.737 --> 18:22.162
It's saying that God understands.

18:23.805 --> 18:29.293
God will bring you to places of still waters because in that he's protecting your faith.

18:29.554 --> 18:31.036
He knows how to protect us.

18:32.138 --> 18:32.658
This is key.

18:33.740 --> 18:34.962
Not just provide for us.

18:35.746 --> 18:36.788
but protect us.

18:39.793 --> 18:41.616
Now you might feel like your faith has failed.

18:42.116 --> 18:51.772
Talk to some people as I've gotten to know many of you and some of you say things about yourself that you failed a lot.

18:51.792 --> 18:53.816
And I'm going to tell you that happens to everybody.

18:55.278 --> 18:56.540
So don't be so hard on yourself.

18:57.682 --> 18:58.884
I know because I'm hard on myself.

18:58.924 --> 18:59.265
I get it.

18:59.285 --> 19:00.767
I get it.

19:00.827 --> 19:02.610
God has had to deal with that in my life.

19:02.914 --> 19:05.157
But I'm going to tell you God always leads us to triumph.

19:05.177 --> 19:05.898
This is who he is.

19:05.958 --> 19:07.040
He is a skilled shepherd.

19:07.060 --> 19:07.320
Amen?

19:08.062 --> 19:08.763
He is skilled.

19:08.783 --> 19:10.245
He knows what he's doing with our life.

19:11.086 --> 19:14.131
Let me give you another image just to try to illustrate what I'm trying to say here.

19:14.171 --> 19:17.856
You'll see an image of a dad with a couple of his boys and a kiddie pool.

19:18.517 --> 19:20.139
Then you'll see an image on the right there.

19:20.179 --> 19:23.064
That's the broads at Lake Winipasaki.

19:24.025 --> 19:26.729
Now skilled dad, this is what he's doing as he's sitting there.

19:26.749 --> 19:27.711
He's playing with his kids.

19:27.751 --> 19:30.855
He provides for them, yes, but he also protects them.

19:30.935 --> 19:32.818
So he's not going to allow them to have

19:32.898 --> 19:36.863
They're little playtime in the middle of the broads in Lake Winnipasaki, right?

19:38.164 --> 19:42.129
He's going to provide and protect them by putting them in a kitty pool.

19:43.090 --> 19:46.474
Now, the little boys there, if they were, they're having a good time, aren't they?

19:46.674 --> 19:48.736
They're having a really good time.

19:49.077 --> 19:51.780
Are they trusting their dad?

19:51.820 --> 19:53.261
For sure.

19:54.182 --> 19:59.669
What would happen if he just said, hey, hey, sons, over the edge, you're going into the broads.

20:00.129 --> 20:00.850
Hope you make it.

20:03.362 --> 20:04.203
What would happen?

20:04.243 --> 20:05.846
What would be in their mind as children?

20:06.266 --> 20:12.476
When they looked at their dad, skilled or unskilled, what would happen inside their heart would be fear and terror.

20:14.078 --> 20:16.241
The skilled shepherd does not do that to us.

20:17.824 --> 20:20.588
He leads us besides still waters.

20:20.668 --> 20:21.469
It's very important.

20:21.950 --> 20:23.392
Very restful waters.

20:23.452 --> 20:24.033
I mentioned that.

20:24.053 --> 20:27.538
That's the literal interpretation of what that's talking about there.

20:28.162 --> 20:32.147
Think of places that there are still waters that you've been around the beauty of it.

20:32.167 --> 20:33.309
I do have a picture of that, right?

20:33.709 --> 20:34.270
Bring this up.

20:34.290 --> 20:35.532
This is a beautiful shot here.

20:35.792 --> 20:36.974
I don't know if it's AI or what.

20:36.994 --> 20:38.035
It looks kind of fake, doesn't it?

20:38.075 --> 20:40.859
But you can use your imagination, right?

20:40.879 --> 20:43.122
And it's like, wow, still waters.

20:43.142 --> 20:43.923
Raging waters.

20:44.043 --> 20:45.405
No, God's not going to bring us there.

20:45.885 --> 20:47.427
He's going to bring us to still waters.

20:48.208 --> 20:52.193
All of that is to protect our faith so that our faith doesn't ultimately fail.

20:53.135 --> 20:55.698
Listen, you are always going to fail forward.

20:57.858 --> 20:58.198
You are.

20:59.260 --> 21:09.311
Now, I've failed and I've tripped and fallen, but I'm not ultimately going to fail in the area of totality.

21:10.752 --> 21:11.413
This doesn't happen.

21:11.433 --> 21:16.398
We just think about that, about our salvation being secure, sure.

21:16.418 --> 21:20.543
We talked about assurance before, but you are going to fail.

21:20.643 --> 21:25.769
And when you fail, you fail, not backwards, forward.

21:26.189 --> 21:27.090
Keep going forward.

21:27.714 --> 21:28.495
This is what we do.

21:29.296 --> 21:31.961
So he makes me, it says, that's the first thought.

21:32.622 --> 21:34.184
And that's not force.

21:34.204 --> 21:35.887
This is more relevatory.

21:36.187 --> 21:36.968
Think about it like this.

21:37.048 --> 21:38.030
God's not forcing me.

21:38.270 --> 21:40.013
He's revealing something to me.

21:40.393 --> 21:43.799
He's revealing next steps to being satisfied in himself.

21:44.520 --> 21:51.250
He's leading me to green pastors, or making me to lie down in green pastors, pardon me, of the gospel.

21:51.554 --> 21:55.838
The second is restorative, so it's relevatory in that first statement.

21:55.858 --> 22:01.584
He makes me, it's restorative in the second one in that he brings me to places of peace.

22:01.944 --> 22:05.388
So think of it like this, grace first, guidance.

22:06.189 --> 22:15.698
It's all about grace in the gospel and then he guides us out of the gospel and through with the gospel for the rest of our lives so that we are able to press on.

22:16.999 --> 22:19.602
God provides, God protects.

22:19.970 --> 22:30.542
And David sees the skill of his shepherd with each crack and crevice that he has to hide in.

22:30.562 --> 22:46.199
And when he gets word that solves close by and he has to leave and keep going, he doesn't know if it's going to be another year, another five years, another 10 years, but he keeps learning the skill of his shepherd because one day he's going to be king.

22:48.001 --> 22:49.042
You see, one day,

22:49.122 --> 22:53.890
You're not going to be king, but you're going to have an influence that's going to be even greater than you have now.

22:53.910 --> 22:56.454
And you're going to have to learn to live in caves.

22:58.437 --> 23:00.340
You're going to have to learn these principles now.

23:01.281 --> 23:02.223
He's preparing you.

23:02.984 --> 23:03.885
He's getting you ready.

23:05.147 --> 23:05.929
This is how he works.

23:06.910 --> 23:10.896
So let me give you those two application principles as way of conclusion.

23:11.477 --> 23:13.941
Letter A would be relinquish any control.

23:14.001 --> 23:15.123
Any control freaks in the house?

23:16.165 --> 23:16.946
Oh, yeah.

23:18.978 --> 23:20.179
A lot of control freaks.

23:20.760 --> 23:21.802
They're mostly over here.

23:24.064 --> 23:25.867
No takers, control freaks.

23:26.607 --> 23:28.149
I'll think of something for you later.

23:29.811 --> 23:31.193
Relinquish any control.

23:31.313 --> 23:34.057
David was in training for a greater calling and destiny.

23:34.998 --> 23:35.759
He would be king.

23:36.880 --> 23:38.883
He has the anointing, doesn't have the position.

23:38.923 --> 23:44.530
He needed some more training and some things before he would fulfill that position many, many years later.

23:44.970 --> 23:47.033
Proverbs 3, 5, and 6 was written by who?

23:47.133 --> 23:47.954
Do you remember?

23:48.514 --> 23:49.195
Let's bring that up.

23:49.255 --> 23:49.595
Thank you.

23:50.597 --> 23:51.818
Yeah, this is David's son.

23:51.878 --> 23:53.500
Now, think about this.

23:53.580 --> 23:58.947
David's watching his dad, you know, experiencing those things that he and his dad would experience.

23:58.967 --> 24:01.931
And he says this, this is very popular versus scripture.

24:02.391 --> 24:04.073
Trust in the Lord with all of your heart.

24:04.914 --> 24:06.656
Do not lean on your own understanding.

24:07.638 --> 24:11.763
In all of your ways, acknowledge him and he will make straight your paths.

24:11.783 --> 24:12.484
Where does he get that?

24:12.504 --> 24:14.366
Now, skill of the shepherd.

24:15.387 --> 24:16.068
He saw his dad.

24:16.128 --> 24:17.650
He understood.

24:18.754 --> 24:20.316
His dad was learning and growing.

24:21.478 --> 24:24.783
Solomon saw all of these things being worked out in his father's life.

24:25.244 --> 24:32.755
The great temptation is to separate ourselves from God's rule over our lives, to take matters into our own hands and try to control them.

24:33.816 --> 24:34.497
I remember this.

24:34.537 --> 24:36.500
We tried adopting three girls many years ago.

24:36.801 --> 24:38.183
I'll tell you the story some other time.

24:38.203 --> 24:38.864
It's so long.

24:39.324 --> 24:41.167
It's such a God story, but it's a hard story.

24:42.149 --> 24:48.498
I can remember trying to adopt them, and it just was not working out, and I really felt like I needed to try to control some things.

24:49.282 --> 24:57.132
See, when you're in a panic or you're feeling like the pressure's on or life is hard or you feel like it's, you're overwhelmed by all the things that's going on in your world.

24:57.152 --> 24:59.976
And I know some of you are overwhelmed with what's going on in your world.

25:00.877 --> 25:02.960
I don't know all the details, but God knows all of that.

25:02.980 --> 25:05.784
If you want to talk about it, I'll be glad to listen and pray with you all of that.

25:06.304 --> 25:11.351
But in the middle of all this hard stuff that we were going through, I'm trying to control everything.

25:12.412 --> 25:14.756
I'm trying to be sovereign, you know, I'm trying to be God.

25:15.637 --> 25:16.658
I think I can do it.

25:17.058 --> 25:19.221
I think that I'm more skilled than God.

25:21.383 --> 25:22.224
This is how we act.

25:23.466 --> 25:26.710
You think that you could skillfully lead your own life?

25:27.971 --> 25:33.338
When we get to the place where we go, God, I am not skilled in this, but you're skilled in shepherding my life.

25:33.358 --> 25:34.299
I trust you with that.

25:34.539 --> 25:35.801
Those verses, we just rent them.

25:36.822 --> 25:38.885
I don't understand what's going on, but I trust you.

25:40.046 --> 25:44.472
When you start to get to that place, you're understanding the skill of the shepherd where David had gotten.

25:45.953 --> 25:46.514
Anyway,

25:46.914 --> 25:50.499
I felt like I was trying to control everything and the Lord gave me a word one day.

25:51.140 --> 25:52.262
And it was a word about Azah.

25:52.282 --> 25:53.163
Now, Azah was a man.

25:53.564 --> 25:57.589
Remember the ark of the covenant was being transported and you had to transport it a certain way.

25:58.210 --> 25:59.512
You couldn't touch it with your hand.

25:59.833 --> 26:02.036
You had to put it on poles, right?

26:02.857 --> 26:05.561
And so they would transport the ark of the covenant on poles.

26:06.142 --> 26:07.203
Can't be touched by people.

26:08.785 --> 26:09.767
So what happened one day?

26:09.827 --> 26:11.489
They were transporting the ark.

26:11.509 --> 26:14.834
It hit a pothole or something in the road there.

26:15.074 --> 26:20.662
It starts to move and this guy, Uzzah goes like this and he tries to steady it with his hand.

26:21.162 --> 26:23.305
What happens to Uzzah?

26:23.325 --> 26:24.907
Yeah, it's a tough story, huh?

26:25.709 --> 26:26.309
Think about that.

26:26.830 --> 26:27.671
It's like, God, why?

26:27.852 --> 26:28.032
Whoa.

26:29.173 --> 26:31.176
This is what God said to me when I was trying to control.

26:32.298 --> 26:35.362
He goes, don't be like Uzzah.

26:35.382 --> 26:37.224
Don't try to touch what I'm doing.

26:38.206 --> 26:39.367
This is what he said to me almost audibly.

26:40.289 --> 26:41.230
Don't touch what I'm doing.

26:41.771 --> 26:44.274
I'm doing something that only I can do.

26:44.962 --> 26:48.307
And you're trying to control it, just like us.

26:50.169 --> 26:52.873
I said, whoa, I pulled back off of that.

26:53.534 --> 26:55.437
And there was this holy reverence in my heart.

26:55.998 --> 26:56.899
And I humbled myself.

26:56.939 --> 26:57.900
And I said, God, I'm sorry.

26:58.561 --> 26:59.743
I'm trying to control everything.

26:59.763 --> 27:00.845
I need to relinquish it.

27:01.445 --> 27:02.567
Relinquish your control.

27:03.248 --> 27:04.069
Open up your hand.

27:05.111 --> 27:05.992
Open it up to God.

27:07.033 --> 27:09.116
I say, God, I'm not going to have a grip on my own life anymore.

27:10.038 --> 27:13.202
I'm going to let go of my grip and relinquish control.

27:14.210 --> 27:16.012
This is how you apply what we're looking at today.

27:17.194 --> 27:18.115
Would you try to do that?

27:19.016 --> 27:19.877
I know it's going to be hard.

27:21.419 --> 27:22.781
It's going to be impossible, in fact.

27:23.883 --> 27:26.526
But the gospel, go back to the gospel, feed on the gospel.

27:27.467 --> 27:27.808
Go there.

27:29.250 --> 27:30.391
And you'll see the power to do it.

27:30.812 --> 27:33.355
Number two, rest in his care, or letter B.

27:34.356 --> 27:35.177
Rest in his care.

27:35.858 --> 27:39.703
Psalm 8, 4, 91, 4, 95, 7, if you want to write these.

27:39.803 --> 27:41.906
And 144, 3, talk about it.

27:42.242 --> 27:44.605
the wonderful, wonderful care of God.

27:45.346 --> 27:47.208
David knew intimately the care of God.

27:48.350 --> 27:51.174
Oh, I don't believe it was an easy journey for David to get to this place.

27:51.234 --> 27:51.935
It took time.

27:52.015 --> 27:53.296
It takes time for you and I.

27:53.336 --> 27:55.239
Don't be too hard on yourself.

27:55.740 --> 27:56.320
It's happening.

27:56.400 --> 27:57.382
God is doing the work.

27:58.123 --> 27:59.865
We're typically not good at resting, right?

28:01.367 --> 28:02.548
Anybody else here like that?

28:02.568 --> 28:03.550
You're not good at resting.

28:03.590 --> 28:06.233
Our culture was, do you know the slogan?

28:06.534 --> 28:07.955
Can you bring up Duncan's watch this?

28:08.016 --> 28:09.938
This is unbelievable.

28:10.018 --> 28:10.759
What's the slogan?

28:10.779 --> 28:11.801
I think it's on the cup there.

28:11.821 --> 28:15.586
I can't quite read it, but America runs on Duncan's.

28:16.347 --> 28:16.648
Yeah.

28:17.929 --> 28:21.835
I know that there's probably 99% of you that are coffee drinkers, right?

28:23.217 --> 28:28.805
Or maybe Red Bull or Monster Drinks, right?

28:29.787 --> 28:33.993
What's the purpose of all of these things that they're making millions and millions and millions of dollars?

28:34.273 --> 28:37.778
That's because you're not getting the rest that you should be getting naturally.

28:38.754 --> 28:42.019
And so what we do is we have to try to stimulate ourselves.

28:43.342 --> 28:47.208
And we need stimulants to be able to have the energy to make it throughout the day.

28:48.651 --> 28:49.773
I'm not against coffee.

28:49.793 --> 28:50.834
I don't personally drink it.

28:50.854 --> 28:51.776
I'm not under crusade.

28:52.397 --> 28:53.679
So don't send me an email with that.

28:55.763 --> 28:57.205
If you want to drink coffee, that's fine.

28:57.245 --> 28:59.248
If you want to have a red bull, that's fine.

28:59.268 --> 29:02.534
I'm just going to make you think a little bit here about rest.

29:04.097 --> 29:04.978
I don't rest well.

29:06.018 --> 29:07.660
I'm not good at, never have been good at it.

29:07.680 --> 29:09.041
It's something the Lord has convicted me on.

29:10.543 --> 29:10.843
Truly.

29:12.445 --> 29:13.386
We all need to rest.

29:14.187 --> 29:15.228
Our rest is not very good.

29:15.269 --> 29:17.011
In fact, I'm going to give you a couple of phrases here.

29:18.192 --> 29:21.876
Monophastic, monophastic sleep is common today.

29:21.896 --> 29:23.117
That's like seven to nine hours.

29:23.478 --> 29:28.203
That's called monophastic, bifastic sleep, is when you might take a nap once in a while.

29:28.804 --> 29:30.886
Then there's polyphastic sleep.

29:31.187 --> 29:34.130
That's many periods in a 24-hour period of time.

29:35.810 --> 29:38.293
Culture in general, there are other countries that do this.

29:38.333 --> 29:41.677
They're polyfastic in the sense of they take multiple naps.

29:41.697 --> 29:43.900
They're resting throughout the day, 24 hours.

29:44.280 --> 29:45.602
We would think that they're what?

29:46.523 --> 29:47.064
Lazy.

29:48.325 --> 29:50.408
I'm thinking now, they're just wise.

29:52.230 --> 29:53.652
I used to think lazy, seriously.

29:54.633 --> 29:55.554
Something's wrong with me.

29:57.417 --> 30:01.181
See, a lot of these cultures, ancient cultures, would rest throughout the day.

30:01.702 --> 30:04.946
They understood rhythms, you know, and things like that.

30:05.762 --> 30:09.186
In fact, the Industrial Revolution is what changed everything, I think, for our culture.

30:10.548 --> 30:19.859
So when you went from rural to urban, and when you went from an agrarian society where you worked with your hands to machinery, then you have everything starting to shift and change.

30:19.899 --> 30:21.120
You had families that changed.

30:21.160 --> 30:23.703
Kids went to work at young age of SNIA families.

30:24.184 --> 30:27.768
The dynamic of the family is changing throughout that period of time.

30:28.969 --> 30:33.074
Beautiful, beautiful technology, beautiful inventions during the Industrial Revolution.

30:33.442 --> 30:35.264
A lot of negative things too came out of that.

30:35.584 --> 30:38.147
Could we say that about modern, even more modern, like the internet?

30:39.008 --> 30:42.732
Some really cool things can happen, but also really negative things can happen with that.

30:43.232 --> 30:44.574
Same with the industrial revolution.

30:46.116 --> 30:49.479
As a result of all of that, we're not getting the rest that we need.

30:52.062 --> 30:56.327
So now we have to jack up our energy levels with stimulants.

30:56.927 --> 31:03.314
I'm going to encourage us and myself, primarily first and foremost, that I would learn the rhythms of rest better.

31:03.874 --> 31:05.076
So that's a public confession.

31:05.456 --> 31:09.341
I want you to keep me accountable to that and say, Chris, are you getting the rest that you need?

31:09.542 --> 31:10.303
Are you sleeping well?

31:11.604 --> 31:13.046
Are you taking those breaks that you need?

31:13.507 --> 31:13.988
Would you do that?

31:14.028 --> 31:14.448
I'm serious.

31:15.470 --> 31:15.710
Would you?

31:16.671 --> 31:17.432
Are you going to pay for it?

31:17.532 --> 31:17.753
Woo!

31:17.973 --> 31:20.957
Yeah.

31:20.977 --> 31:24.302
I saw the care of God for me many years ago, four years ago, actually.

31:24.322 --> 31:25.623
I was in ICU for a week.

31:26.745 --> 31:31.051
I had never been to the hospital for anything other than to visit people in my churches.

31:32.412 --> 31:33.554
I mean, I saw my tonsils.

31:35.810 --> 31:38.633
So I'm in ICU now, for a week.

31:39.975 --> 31:40.756
What did I learn there?

31:42.758 --> 31:43.999
Skill of the shepherd, for sure.

31:45.341 --> 31:50.847
But I had to rely on the rest and the care of those wonderful doctors and nurses.

31:52.229 --> 31:53.130
So there were lots of them.

31:53.591 --> 31:54.271
There were dozens.

31:54.351 --> 31:55.813
I mean, that was in rough shape.

31:56.934 --> 32:00.358
And so I got all kinds of tubes sticking out of my neck and stuff like that.

32:00.439 --> 32:03.442
And I'm laying there, couldn't do anything for myself.

32:05.666 --> 32:07.368
But God was teaching me some great things.

32:09.290 --> 32:10.732
Just trust them to care for me.

32:12.053 --> 32:13.695
Trust God, trust them.

32:13.735 --> 32:15.657
That's what I had to do.

32:16.258 --> 32:18.020
Can I encourage you, rest in the care of God?

32:19.341 --> 32:20.042
He cares for you.

32:21.264 --> 32:21.904
He really does.

32:23.146 --> 32:23.927
So here's the end of it.

32:24.227 --> 32:27.971
Number one, God provided for us, provides for us just enough faith to move forward.

32:27.991 --> 32:31.495
Number two, God protects our faith so it won't ultimately fail.

32:32.016 --> 32:34.098
Application is relinquish any control.

32:34.530 --> 32:35.631
Rest in his care.

32:36.172 --> 32:36.412
Amen?

32:37.273 --> 32:38.734
Let's read Psalm 23 out loud.

32:38.754 --> 32:40.116
If we can, again, out loud.

32:40.156 --> 32:41.317
The Lord is my shepherd.

32:41.877 --> 32:42.978
I shall not want.

32:43.179 --> 32:45.341
He makes me lie down in green pastures.

32:45.861 --> 32:47.903
He leads me beside still waters.

32:48.344 --> 32:49.825
He restores my soul.

32:50.366 --> 32:53.709
He leads me in paths of righteousness for his namesake.

32:54.250 --> 32:58.234
Even though I walk through the valley of the shadow of death, I will fear no evil.

32:58.614 --> 32:59.575
For you are with me.

33:00.016 --> 33:02.418
Your rod and your staff, they comfort me.

33:02.594 --> 33:05.858
You prepare a table before me in the presence of my enemies.

33:06.298 --> 33:09.342
You anoint my head with oil, my cup overflows.

33:09.783 --> 33:14.068
And surely goodness and mercy shall follow me all the days of my life.

33:14.528 --> 33:16.911
And I shall dwell in the house of the Lord forever.

33:17.792 --> 33:20.976
Glory to you, Lord, the skilled master shepherd.

33:22.077 --> 33:24.220
There is nothing too difficult for you, O Lord.

33:25.201 --> 33:26.443
And so we rest in that.

33:27.264 --> 33:28.545
We relinquish control.

33:28.605 --> 33:32.530
We admit to you that we've had a grip on our own lives or circumstances.

33:32.642 --> 33:35.925
We're trying to be God, we're trying to be sovereign, trying to be in control.

33:35.945 --> 33:42.092
Oh God, may we release our grispen, relinquish our control, and may we rest in your care for us.

33:42.172 --> 33:43.834
You know exactly what you're doing.

33:44.955 --> 33:47.157
You know exactly how to shepherd our lives.

33:47.798 --> 33:49.740
You make us lie down in green pastures.

33:49.760 --> 33:57.588
You give us just what we need, enough faith, then to move out of our comfort, out of the cave of comfort, on to the rest of the journey.

33:57.968 --> 33:59.890
It's hard, scary,

34:00.834 --> 34:08.686
At times, Lord, we think that we're going to be just overcome by everything, but then you show up and you show that you are so skilled.

34:09.447 --> 34:10.749
You know exactly what you're doing.

34:10.769 --> 34:13.273
You protect our faith so it won't ultimately fail.

34:14.735 --> 34:18.661
When we do trip and fall, which is many times in our lifetime, we will fail forward.

34:19.803 --> 34:29.618
Please give encouragement to those in this room or watching online that they would hear your voice on this, that they would know that you certainly know what you're doing with their lives.

34:30.050 --> 34:31.653
In Jesus' mighty name, amen?

34:32.434 --> 34:36.220
You are left.

34:36.240 --> 34:40.147
Thanks for listening to the Crossway Christian Church's Middleford campus sermon podcast.

34:40.448 --> 34:48.141
If you like to plug into the life of our community or have any questions that we might be able to answer, visit our website at crosswaycc.org to connect with us.

34:48.161 --> 34:49.423
Until next time, we can be with you.

34:49.743 --> 34:51.346
May the Lord bless you and keep you.

